==English==
===Noun===
'''norm''' (''plural'' '''norms''')
{{wikipedia}}
#('''the norm''') That which is [[normal]].
#:''Unemployment is the norm in this part of the country.''
#{{analysis}} A function, , denoted |''v''| or ||''v''||, that [[map]]s [[vector]]s to non-negative [[scalar]]s and has the following properties:
##|''v''| > 0 or |''v''| = 0 [[iff]] ''v'' = 0;
##given a scalar ''k'', |''kv''| = |''k''|.|''v''|, where |''k''| is the [[absolute value]] of ''k'';
##given two vectors ''v'' and ''w'', |''v'' + ''w''| &le; |''v''| + |''w''| (the [[triangle inequality]]).

